The primary embodiment of power is the One Ring, a symbol of absolute control and domination.

The primary source of power in Middle-earth is the One Ring, forged by the Dark Lord Sauron to enslave and dominate all other beings.
The Ring's corrupting influence is so potent that even the strongest of wills, such as Gandalf and Boromir, to name a few, are tempted by its promise of absolute authority.
Throughout the series, characters are tempted by the Ring's promise of unlimited power, to varying degrees of success.
